File: Technicians analyse PCR samples amid the COVID-19 pandemic. AFP/Yamil Lage JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 22,910 COVID-19 new cases in the last 24 hours. That brings the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 2,135,246. READ: COVID-19 | Gauteng remains epicentre - Health Dept A total of 75,276 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours. There are also 208,847 active cases in the country. A further 460 COVID-19 related deaths have been reported, bringing total fatalities to 63,499 to date.